headline: Hershey Stock Jumps 11% as New Product Demand Fuels Growth Debate
summary: Wondering if Hershey stock is a sweet deal or overhyped? Here is a look at what really matters for its value right now. Shares have risen 10.9% in the past 30 days, bringing the stock up 11.4% year-to-date, which may indicate renewed optimism around Hershey’s growth prospects. Much of this recent movement has followed heightened investor interest in the broader food and beverage sector, with coverage focusing on supply chain stability and evolving consumer spending patterns.
